A reporting framework is not only a dashboard. It is a repeatable system that connects KPI definitions, reporting cadence, audience needs, and follow-up actions.

## Core elements

- KPI dictionary with clear formulas
- Role-based dashboard views
- Weekly and monthly reporting cadence
- Ownership for each indicator
- Action tracking linked to performance changes

## Typical failure points

- Too many metrics and no priority
- Inconsistent definitions across teams
- Reporting without operational follow-up

## Practical recommendation

Start with a small KPI set that directly supports operational decisions. Expand only after the team can use the first version consistently.
